asset.name: LOOKS RARE ---------VIDEO STILL #1
asset.description:
A film short by Victor Reyes Studio ----------Video Still#1

Sound Track by Loopsdigi

Infatuation within the Crypto collectible world has led to an entire short hand vocabulary used to communicate and instigate movement "it looks Rare" the turn of phrase used to indicate perceived value as status. Also a pun as many of the images labeled with that idiom are multiples in the Tens of thousands. Amid this roiling sub culture is a current pushing  against the structural walls of art and finance. A boiler room of incongruent norms and tropes. Are we headed off the cliff? is the end Nigh? I am not sure? But this Looks Rare.

Penny dreadfuls were cheap popular serial literature produced during the nineteenth century in the United Kingdom. The pejorative term is roughly interchangeable with penny horrible, penny awful, and penny blood. The term typically referred to a story published in weekly parts of 8 to 16 pages, each costing one penny. The subject matter of these stories was typically sensational, focusing on the exploits of detectives, criminals, or supernatural entities. First published in the 1830s, penny dreadfuls featured characters such as Sweeney Todd, Dick Turpin, Varney the Vampire and Spring-heeled Jack. (Wikipedia)

asset.name: Midnight Calm
asset.description:
The waters were incredibly still, only interrupted by quiet splashing. The hero was rowing the boat in pitch darkness. Feeling exhausted she paused, unsure of her destination. Her instinct brought her here, but she wondered if she had made a mistake. She was about to turn back when the night sky grew brighter, suddenly illuminated by dancing lights. She was instantly mesmerized by the gorgeous sight, breath-taken by the vivid colors that even made the clouds glow.

She noticed a rift in the sky, the thick darkness that slashed through the lights. There the cosmic energy was leaking through. She felt her magic returning and it was washing away any lingering darkness off her magical cloak. Feeling immensely grateful, she was more appreciative of simple things, realizing their transience.

She heard a sound calling out to her- the voice seemed to be all around her. Then she noticed shadows approaching beneath the water's surface, a gigantic creature and her young. She stayed calm and concentrated on what they were trying to tell her.

asset.name: Neeuv
asset.description:
Can you imagine a 'choose your own adventure style' 3D interactive webXR story on the Ethereum blockchain? Where you would hop on different devices to explore, interact and save what you altered in a persistent multiplayer adventure from 3D browser desktop to WebAR to WebVR experiences. 

A story which evolves being updated by artists over time. One that is artist led as-well as audience led. Your choices and saves within the story at times informs the artists for their subsequent future version updates to the story. A story distributed using the blockchain as a medium and harnessing the full power of web technologies. 

This is the world 'Neeuv' exists in, as she jumps though her most recent portal in the metaverse!

asset.name: PLASTIC II
asset.description:
PLASTIC II is the second artwork in the PLASTIC series. 

This series attempts to viscerally portray the emotions I feel when seeing all the littered plastic on the ground. Every time I go for my daily walk around the park, I see it everywhere and it sickens me to my core. I feel such disdain for the human race when I see our lack of care for the planet we live on and all the beautiful animals that end up dying because of our actions. Not only are we destroying other life forms, but we are also killing ourselves. Not yet, but eventually it will catch up with us when our future generations pay the price. 

Each day on my walk, I end up collecting between 5 - 10 pieces of plastic. I feel compelled to, but sometimes I honestly wish I could just not look down to see it all, and live in ignorant bliss.

asset.name: THIS ARTWORK IS WORTH MORE ON SUPERRARE [RGB/RED VARIANT EDITION]
asset.description:
The controversial conceptual statement piece originally minted on Foundation, is offered as limited edition variants in this special collection. These variants will only be offered once, and no other variants will be minted in the future. 

ABOUT THE ORIGINAL 1/1 PIECE:
Deeply rooted in conceptual art, ‘THIS ARTWORK IS WORTH MORE ON SUPERRARE’, actively engages the viewer by offering a statement which invites critical debate and discourse on topics relevant to the burgeoning culture of NFT art.

Its visual elements typify the artist’s stylistic penchant for blending typography with free flow gestural painting, characteristic of  abstract expressionism. The purchase of the original 1/1 piece by legendary NFT art patron and collector, 888, is in itself an affirmation that adds to the cultural narrative; as it is now part of an ever-growing prestigious collection of NFT art. 

As the lexicon of NFT art continues to be defined by art critics, academics, and historians, the use of blockchain technology as a layer component of the artist’s creation in exploring NFTs as a medium of expression, historically marks the artwork’s significance in form and style.

asset.description:

September 2021, 1/1 on KnownOrigin

A lament on the grotesque..

Part of the Penny Dreadful Collection

...

Penny dreadfuls were cheap popular serial literature produced during the nineteenth century in the United Kingdom. The pejorative term is roughly interchangeable with penny horrible, penny awful, and penny blood. The term typically referred to a story published in weekly parts of 8 to 16 pages, each costing one penny. The subject matter of these stories was typically sensational, focusing on the exploits of detectives, criminals, or supernatural entities. First published in the 1830s, penny dreadfuls featured characters such as Sweeney Todd, Dick Turpin, Varney the Vampire and Spring-heeled Jack. (Wikipedia)

"Forget not that I shall come back to you.

A little while, and my longing shall gather dust and foam for another body.
A little while, a moment of rest upon the wind, and another woman shall bear me.

Farewell to you and the youth I have spent with you.It was but yesterday we met in a dream.
You have sung to me in my aloneness, and I of your longings have built a tower in the sky.

But now our sleep has fled and our dream is over, and it is no longer dawn.
The noontide is upon us and our half waking has turned to fuller day, and we must part.     

If in the twilight of memory we should meet once more, we shall speak again together and you shall sing to me a deeper song.

And if our hands should meet in another dream we shall build another tower in the sky."

asset.name: Trinity - 50/50 Edition
asset.description:
The second collaboration between Swiss Artist Dario De Siena and Bay Area Artist Gabe Weis was born in the early days of our NFT journey. The plan for the onset was to drop two collaborative NFTs that would showcase our different styles and let each artists shine.

This NFT started as a 36 by 36” collage on canvas using one of Dario’s iconic women as the focal point. Gabe chose to add two figures to either side of the main female to show the multitudes that we all live in. Together these three intertwined figures form a trinity of form and spirit.
We hope that as we grow this NFT community that we can always appreciate friendship, collaboration and joy.  

As part of this drop we will do a raffle of the 36” by 36” original collage on canvas. We will do the drawing during an IG live using a random number generator. Numbers will be given in the order of purchase.

The drawing will take place on the Wednesday after all 50 of the NFTs are sold. We will post on both of our IG stories for the lucky winner.

Penny dreadfuls were cheap popular serial literature produced during the nineteenth century in the United Kingdom. The pejorative term is roughly interchangeable with penny horrible, penny awful, and penny blood. The term typically referred to a story published in weekly parts of 8 to 16 pages, each costing one penny. The subject matter of these stories was typically sensational, focusing on the exploits of detectives, criminals, or supernatural entities. First published in the 1830s, penny dreadfuls featured characters such as Sweeney Todd, Dick Turpin, Varney the Vampire and Spring-heeled Jack. (Wikipedia)

asset.description:
“Oh Andy honey.. Please get me a bunny. Please! Please!!” - Laurie Anderson (The Rotowhirl from The Ugly One With The Jewels And Other Stories) 

Digital Image by Hulki Okan Tabak. Limited Edition of 5. Minted November 25, 2020. 

The Bunny Project started in November 2020. The 1st phase of this project will span digital images, photography techniques, out of control GIFs and a custom soundtrack with a glitchy bunny.

The idea is an interplay between the boundary of the funny and scary epitomized in a digital child bunny borne out of Artbreeder parents. Primary intention was to have visual fun with some surprise elements.

This is a 3 piece subset in the Bunny Project. This subset is aptly named The Bunny Melts or The Melting Bunny or whatever remains.. One piece in the subset is The Bunny with all its originality. Still a child, parent already revealed - The Bunny is the inspiration. Then there is the GIF that will come after the other digital image. The Bunny melts in the GIF. Sad.. Ahhh in the middle is The Bunny that is Out of It All.. That's a glitched hurt bunny or something that is seeking to avoid. Your call..

The Melting Bunny will be followed with wackier GIFs and sometime in the line up The Hard Bunny. Bunnies all around..  

This is a 300dpi digital image of 7000 x 7000 dimensions.

asset.name: [Un]seen Warsaw
asset.description:
[Un]seen Warsaw is a project that aims to explore Poland's capital architecture through Artificial Intelligence generated images. The project is an invitation to take a virtual walk on the streets of Warsaw that do not exist and were generated by training a generative Machine Learning model on real photographs. 

The artificially created images are meant to dispense a familiar feeling to a viewer accustomed to Warsaw architecture. At the same time, they bring a sense of disorientation to the surface since the places observed cannot be precisely located as they do not stand in the real world. The project’s purpose is to provide a new aspect to recognizable sites and an invitation to crossroads and encounter corners that don’t truly exist within the city, but that can be perceived as simultaneously reliable and convincing.  A closer look reveals how the fluid transition between reality and fiction can bring about exotic and alienating objects disclosed by the deformation of buildings as if a mad architect had given the city a whimsical composition.

The AI training model is based on 3000 still images shot by the artist along the streets of Warsaw in November 2020. Each of the works has been assigned an address in the virtual multidimensional space by using real Warsaw street names and numbers that were taken as input to generate those particular images. While such an address usually does not exist on the map of Warsaw, the project assumes the role of imagining an alternative augmented version of the city.

This work has been awarded the best award in the Digital Ars 2020 contest dedicated to art creation with AI.
The piece has been showcased at XXIV Generative Art International Conference and Digital Ars festival.
Featured in CLOT Mag, Aktivist, Cikados and other international publications.

asset.name: USA 1870: Deconstructing G
asset.description:
Photograph by Hulki Okan Tabak. Limited Edition of 1. Minted November 10, 2020. Exclusively for KnownOrigin.

George Washington was an American political leader, military general, statesman, and Founding Father who served as the first president of the United States from 1789 to 1797. Previously, he led Patriot forces to victory in the nation's War for Independence. He appears on a United States stamp collection from 1870 and I have started to build this piece from an actual used physical copy of that stamp.

At this juncture in the series, the image is deconstructed to be reconstructed. It is manipulated, glitched, defocused and several layers of specific proprietary filters and experimentation is applied. This is the transition piece to the final mood video.

This is the 4th piece of a 5 artwork series that involves Edwin Stanton and George Washington from actual used 1870 stamps. The series consists of 4 digitally manipulated photographs and a video file. Various digital tools were used in creating the final images.

"She wove her own fishnets from the finest silk imported from the Andalusian mountains. She had been weaving since she was little, helping her grandmother with the large fishing nets at the dockside. asset.name: When The Horse Is No More A Horse
asset.description:
When The Horse Is No More A Horse by Mad Monk, 10 Editions, September 2021, KnownOrigin

is
a piece
about glitch and
more than that of
some admiration for the publication
however grotesque it was that it
provided an escapade for the burdened everydayperson.

Part of the Penny Dreadful Collection

...

Penny dreadfuls were cheap popular serial literature produced during the nineteenth century in the United Kingdom. The pejorative term is roughly interchangeable with penny horrible, penny awful, and penny blood. The term typically referred to a story published in weekly parts of 8 to 16 pages, each costing one penny. The subject matter of these stories was typically sensational, focusing on the exploits of detectives, criminals, or supernatural entities. First published in the 1830s, penny dreadfuls featured characters such as Sweeney Todd, Dick Turpin, Varney the Vampire and Spring-heeled Jack. (Wikipedia)

asset.name: The Matrix
asset.description:
A pod is a receptacle where synthetically created humans are inserted and hardwired into becoming part of the power plant and virtually integrated the Matrix.

Humans are grown in the Fetus fields and, based on Morpheus' description of pods, are immediately connected by myriad umbilicals that not only provide the body with sustenance, but draw heat energy from the body to power the Machines and their city. They are gathered and transferred from by Harvesters to full pods in the power plant.

Central to the control of a human in the pod is a data probe that is firmly and permanently attached to the headjack, which provides connectivity of the human's mind into the Matrix. Each human pod can be compared to a radio station; a carrier signal for each human mind transmits and receives data from the Source to process information needed to form the neural-interactive world of the Matrix. Millions and millions of these pods are connected to cylindrical towers that form the power plant.

The pejorative term is roughly interchangeable with penny horrible, penny awful, and penny blood. The term typically referred to a story published in weekly parts of 8 to 16 pages, each costing one penny. asset.name: Zerø Day ØB$$e$$iŌn
asset.description: A few days ago I was Innerspace Gallery in DTLA. Earlier in the day I had eaten a bunch of mushrooms and MDA. JesusHands was gluing pounds of Cannabis flower onto a wooden slab for a promotion for the Gentlemen while crews of film makers were documenting the process with tons of cameras. Don Raph and Calen Blake were both making art nearby. I proceeded to make the back of this jacket - called "0 Day Obsession". I used a variety of mixed media - paper, stickers, tapes, etc. I no longer have the flagged-out fanny pack nor the jacket. Both were gifted last night - the fanny pack to an art collector - and the jacket to a homeless man at 3am who was cold and needed some warmth. This piece is an ode to hacking, life hacking, art hacking, crypto, doing the right thing & all the things that make life so beautiful.

asset.name: Ready To Die
asset.description:
His words spoke for millions, and opened eyes like mine to a totally different world.

Neural Impressionism is a style by which a computer using neural networks recreates an image based off of other images, then styled with yet other images many times over. The results of this process is then put into photoshop and pieced together over several months in an emotional, random, and pantsy type effort. This piece started in January of 2019 and finished in April 2019.  

There is a still photo located on Saatchi Art, only when an owner who hold one of these five tokens as well as a piece from Saatchi can the art be considered in its whole form. The Saatchi Art can be found here:  https://www.saatchiart.com/print/New-Media-Ready-To-Die/1238933/4969875/view?sku=P204-U1238933-A6106407-T2-F

asset.name: Napcap Induction Cap
asset.description:
“Fatigue bent her like decades, and she was overjoyed to see the blinking yellow sign of a Napcap rental facility.
A few meager credits remained on her debit card. She would invest them in a decent snooze.
She punched her card into the Napcap's slot. The lid lifted and she crawled inside. It shooshed down. The inside received her as a womb...
Ordinary human sleep varies greatly in depth and quality, a vestigial remembrance of the time when Homo habilis need to cycle between deep sleep and near waking, lest in a comalike slumber he fall prey to carnivores. In the napcap a client became an instant yoga master, able to stay in the deepest states for hours, increasing the value of each minute's rest manyfold.”

From “Saturn's Race” by Larry Niven (w/S. Barnes). 
Published by Tor in 2000.

asset.name: Midnight Calm
asset.description:
The waters were incredibly still, only interrupted by quiet splashing. The hero was rowing the boat in pitch darkness. Feeling exhausted she paused, unsure of her destination. Her instinct brought her here, but she wondered if she had made a mistake. She was about to turn back when the night sky grew brighter, suddenly illuminated by dancing lights. She was instantly mesmerized by the gorgeous sight, breath-taken by the vivid colors that even made the clouds glow.

She noticed a rift in the sky, the thick darkness that slashed through the lights. There the cosmic energy was leaking through. She felt her magic returning and it was washing away any lingering darkness off her magical cloak. Feeling immensely grateful, she was more appreciative of simple things, realizing their transience.

She heard a sound calling out to her- the voice seemed to be all around her. Then she noticed shadows approaching beneath the water's surface, a gigantic creature and her young. She stayed calm and concentrated on what they were trying to tell her.

assets.name: On The 5th Day We Were Free'd
assets.description:
A 5 day collaboration, myself, Jay Delay , Brandi Kyle , drangonate and Stina Jones

The piece is meant to resemble feelings of the artists working day, passing on each day to another artist to create through their emotional struggle or intent. Overall the piece to me is a vibrant mix of expressing the need to create, influence and remain unconstrained across that deep desire to dream of more.

Another element to this experiment that was unclear until the end was we are all influenced to do things in a certain way, even how we process a creation and thoughts which we think are unique may be influenced......this was a great way of partially breaking the mold, that any form of programmed creation for a single entity could not be defined here.

Something that is unqualified emotionally but of our mix together. 

A landmark piece.

The pejorative term is roughly interchangeable with penny horrible, penny awful, and penny blood. The term typically referred to a story published in weekly parts of 8 to 16 pages, each costing one penny. The subject matter of these stories was typically sensational, focusing on the exploits of detectives, criminals, or supernatural entities. asset.description:
FELIX studied a dataset of Bryan Brinkman's work, training on it and slowly studying Brinkman's palette. At some point during training, "darkness" was introduced; the color black added a fascinating contrast to Brinkman's technique. Brinkman then interpreted the outputs, and created his own animations over the canvas born from his portfolio.

Two pieces were born from the dance between FELIX and Brinkman; a 1/1 and a 5/5. This is the latter, named "Flower".

asset.name: I AM
asset.description:
Work gives us a title, a role, a sense of stability and a paycheck. It can easily become part of our identity, and it can be hard to separate ourselves from it. But things happen. The company might face unexpected trouble, or you might have to leave a position. If you cling too tightly to the material aspects of a job, or invest your entire identity in it, the sense of purpose and joy comes to depend on something which is always uncertain. This doesn’t mean we shouldn’t become invested in our work. Moreover, as we go on with our daily life, we forget that we are not our job title or the activity which occupies most of our time, and in forgetfulness, we begin to identify our own existence with that activity. 

What happens if you identify so closely with your work that hating your job means also hating yourself? Psychologists use the term “enmeshment” to describe a situation where the boundaries between people become blurred, and individual identities lose importance. Enmeshment prevents the development of a stable, independent sense of self. While identifying closely with your career isn’t necessarily bad, it makes you vulnerable to a painful identity crisis if you burn out, get laid off, or retire. Individuals in these situations frequently suffer anxiety, depression, and despair. By claiming back some time for yourself and diversifying your activities and relationships, you can build a more balanced and robust identity in line with your values. Perhaps, you could find a path which can lead you to reconnect with your true self.

This artwork portrays people with a visible identification of who they think they are (identifying with their activity, job etc). We can say that we are this and that, but we are also a friend, a parent or a son, a husband or wife, a volunteer or our hobby, and then we realize that we are so many things and yet these are just labels and layers. If we just stop for a moment and look inside, we might be able to remember what we truly are.

asset.name: Napcap Induction Cap
asset.description:
“Fatigue bent her like decades, and she was overjoyed to see the blinking yellow sign of a Napcap rental facility.
A few meager credits remained on her debit card. She would invest them in a decent snooze.
She punched her card into the Napcap's slot. The lid lifted and she crawled inside. It shooshed down. The inside received her as a womb...
Ordinary human sleep varies greatly in depth and quality, a vestigial remembrance of the time when Homo habilis need to cycle between deep sleep and near waking, lest in a comalike slumber he fall prey to carnivores. In the napcap a client became an instant yoga master, able to stay in the deepest states for hours, increasing the value of each minute's rest manyfold.”

From “Saturn's Race” by Larry Niven (w/S. Barnes). 
Published by Tor in 2000.

Artwork was created using https://ganbreeder.app/ 
GANbreeder app was created by Joel Simon https://www.joelsimon.net/ 

 Artwork Lineage: https://ganbreeder.app/lineage?k=74de0ae2dee99891e46f2df9
